message: "If you use this dataset or pipeline, please cite both the manuscript and the archived deposit as below."
title: "soap-sbar-llm-benchmark: Quantifying Safety-Critical Information Loss in LLM-Generated Clinical Handoffs (Data, Code, and Materials)"
abstract: >
  Reproducibility package for a priority-stratified, three-stage automated
  evaluation pipeline that quantifies safety-critical omission (SCO) — the
  proportion of high-priority clinical facts completely omitted — when four
  commercial large language models (GPT-4o, GPT-5.5, Claude Opus 4.5, and
  Gemini 2.5 Flash-Lite) translate Japanese SOAP nursing records into SBAR
  handoff summaries. Includes 9 source SOAP scenarios, 180 annotated fact tags,
  2,160 generated SBAR records, the three-stage pipeline (deterministic Stage 1,
  dual cross-vendor AI judges Stage 2, arbiter Stage 3), the gap-fixed
  consensus scores, an independent registered nurse's blinded re-scoring of a
  400-cell subset and independent priority re-labelling for inter-rater
  reliability, and all analysis scripts.
